Program: Outlook
Title: 10/03/2010
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/p006hrsl
Last Broadcast Date: Thu 11 Mar 2010
Personal stories behind the news from all over the world. With Matthew Bannister. Haiti school children; Zanzibar electricity crisis; the girl who sleeps for two weeks at a time Haiti school Outlook hears from the children having lessons in tents, after their school was destroyed in the recent earthquake. Zanzibar electricity After three months of no power, electricity has been restored in Zanzibar. But how did people cope during the crisis? Freddie Boswell reports. Sleeping beauty Fifteen-year-old Louise Ball has Kleine-Levin Syndrome - the so-called "sleeping beauty" syndrome. She sleeps for up to two weeks at a time, and tells us she once slept through an entire family holiday. Show less